The paper focuses on visual question answering, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a method that incorporates structured human knowledge, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed method also involves memory networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
